Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @Carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄2-inch-thick half moons. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, half the @Cumin{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), and a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Roast on the top rack until tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} and half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings); cook, stirring frequently, until garlic powder is fragrant and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in 3⁄4 cup water (11⁄4 cups for 4 servings) and a big pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce} and roughly chop @Pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP @Olive Oil{2%TBSP}, 1 tsp @Salt{1%tsp}, and 1⁄2 tsp @Sugar{1/2%tsp} until sugar is dissolved (all the vinegar, 4 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp salt, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Add tomatoes and toss until thoroughly coated.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Once veggies are roasted and couscous is cooked, stir into bowl with marinated tomatoes; add @Spinach{5%ounce} and toss until spinach is slightly wilted.

Divide spinach salad between #bowls{} and top with @Feta Cheese{1/2%cup}(crumbled) and pistachios. Serve.

Slice chicken crosswise. Top salad with chicken and garnish with feta and pistachios.